# Tawjih V4 — Full Platform Scaffold with Docker

Build the Tawjih V4 AI-native study abroad platform from the ground up using Docker Compose, based on the 2871-line spec (18 modules, 30+ exams, 13 languages).

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Scope**: This plan covers the **initial project scaffold only** — Docker infrastructure, backend skeleton (FastAPI + all DB connections), frontend skeleton (React + Vite + React Router with route stubs), auth API, and database migrations. Actual module logic (exam simulation engine, AI career advisor, etc.) will follow in subsequent phases.

> [!WARNING]
> **OpenAI / WhatsApp keys**: The `.env` file will have placeholder values. You'll need to supply real API keys for AI features to work.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Frontend approach**: The `stitch_the_mentor_prd` folder has 60 pre-designed HTML pages (using TailwindCSS CDN + Lexend font). The React app will reference these designs and progressively convert them into React components. For the initial scaffold, the landing page and auth pages will be fully integrated; other pages will have route stubs.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Docker Infrastructure

#### [NEW] [docker-compose.yml](file:///c:/DEV/Tawjih%20V4/docker-compose.yml)
All 7 services orchestrated:

| Service | Image | Ports | Volumes |
|---------|-------|-------|---------|
| `db` | postgres:16 | 5433:5432 | `pgdata` |
| `mongo` | mongo:7 | 27018:27017 | `mongodata` |
| `minio` | minio/minio | 9001:9001, 9002:9000 | `miniodata` |
| `redis` | redis:7 | 6380:6379 | `redisdata` |
| `backend` | ./backend Dockerfile | 8089:8000 | Source mounted for dev |
| `frontend` | ./frontend Dockerfile | 3089:80 | Source mounted for dev |
| `worker` | ./backend Dockerfile (celery) | — | Shares backend code |

#### [NEW] [.env](file:///c:/DEV/Tawjih%20V4/.env)
Environment variables as per spec section 26.2: `DATABASE_URL`, `MONGODB_URL`, `MINIO_*`, `REDIS_URL`, `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `JWT_SECRET`, `ENCRYPTION_KEY`, etc.

---

### Backend (FastAPI)

#### [NEW] [backend/Dockerfile](file:///c:/DEV/Tawjih%20V4/backend/Dockerfile)
Python 3.12 slim image, pip install requirements, uvicorn entrypoint on port 8000.

#### [NEW] [backend/requirements.txt](file:///c:/DEV/Tawjih%20V4/backend/requirements.txt)
Core deps: `fastapi`, `uvicorn[standard]`, `sqlalchemy[asyncio]`, `asyncpg`, `alembic`, `motor`, `pymongo`, `minio`, `redis[hiredis]`, `celery[redis]`, `python-jose[cryptography]`, `passlib[bcrypt]`, `pydantic[email]`, `python-multipart`, `httpx`.

#### [NEW] [backend/app/main.py](file:///c:/DEV/Tawjih%20V4/backend/app/main.py)
FastAPI application with CORS, health endpoint (`/api/health`), and router includes for auth, profile, prep, career, roadmap, documents, community, gamification, admin, marketplace, financial, housing, mentors, visa-prep, learn, copilot, notifications, integrations.

#### [NEW] [backend/app/core/config.py](file:///c:/DEV/Tawjih%20V4/backend/app/core/config.py)
Pydantic Settings class loading from environment variables.

#### [NEW] [backend/app/core/database.py](file:///c:/DEV/Tawjih%20V4/backend/app/core/database.py)
- Async SQLAlchemy engine + session factory for PostgreSQL
- Motor async client for MongoDB
- MinIO client
- Redis async client

#### [NEW] [backend/app/core/security.py](file:///c:/DEV/Tawjih%20V4/backend/app/core/security.py)
JWT token creation/verification, bcrypt password hashing, OAuth2 dependency for route protection.

#### [NEW] [backend/app/models/](file:///c:/DEV/Tawjih%20V4/backend/app/models/)
SQLAlchemy ORM models matching spec schemas:
- `user.py` — users table (sec 3.3)
- `student_profile.py` — student_profiles (sec 3.4)
- `school.py` — schools (sec 3.5)
- `program.py` — programs (sec 3.6)
- `exam.py` — exam_attempts, exam_progress (sec 5.5-5.6)
- `roadmap.py` — roadmap_templates, user_roadmaps (sec 6.3-6.4)
- `notification.py` — notification_queue (sec 9.5)
- `scholarship.py` — scholarships (sec 10.2)
- `gamification.py` — user_gamification, study_groups (sec 15.3-15.4)
- `mentor.py` — mentors (sec 12.3)
- `marketplace.py` — service_providers, service_reviews (sec 14.2-14.3)
- `visa.py` — visa_mock_sessions (sec 18.4)
- `learning.py` — learning_progress (sec 19.6)
- `integration.py` — platform_connections (sec 17.4)
- `pre_departure.py` — pre_departure_checklists (sec 11.4)

#### [NEW] [backend/app/routers/auth.py](file:///c:/DEV/Tawjih%20V4/backend/app/routers/auth.py)
Full auth flow: `POST /api/auth/register`, `POST /api/auth/login`, `POST /api/auth/refresh`, `POST /api/auth/verify-email`.

#### [NEW] [backend/app/routers/](file:///c:/DEV/Tawjih%20V4/backend/app/routers/) (stub routers)
One file per module with placeholder endpoints:
`profile.py`, `prep.py`, `career.py`, `roadmap.py`, `documents.py`, `community.py`, `gamification.py`, `admin.py`, `marketplace.py`, `financial.py`, `housing.py`, `mentors.py`, `visa_prep.py`, `learn.py`, `copilot.py`, `notifications.py`, `integrations.py`

#### [NEW] [backend/alembic.ini](file:///c:/DEV/Tawjih%20V4/backend/alembic.ini) + [backend/alembic/](file:///c:/DEV/Tawjih%20V4/backend/alembic/)
Alembic configuration for PostgreSQL migrations. Initial migration creates all tables.

