### Frontend (React + Vite)

#### [NEW] [frontend/Dockerfile](file:///c:/DEV/Tawjih%20V4/frontend/Dockerfile)
Multi-stage: Node 20 for build, Nginx for serve. Dev mode uses Vite dev server.

#### [NEW] [frontend/](file:///c:/DEV/Tawjih%20V4/frontend/)
React 18 + Vite project initialized via `npm create vite@latest`:
- `src/App.jsx` — React Router with all routes defined
- `src/main.jsx` — App entry point
- `src/pages/` — Page components (Landing, Login, Register, Dashboard, etc.)
- `src/components/` — Shared components (Header, Footer, Layout)
- `src/api/` — API client with axios + JWT interceptor
- `src/contexts/` — AuthContext for user state
- `tailwind.config.js` — TailwindCSS v3 with the design system colors from Stitch designs
- `nginx.conf` — SPA-friendly Nginx config

#### Frontend Routes (matching spec + Stitch designs)
All 60+ Stitch page directories will be mapped to React Router routes. The initial scaffold includes working implementations for:
- `/` — Landing page (from [landing_page/code.html](file:///c:/DEV/Tawjih%20V4/stitch_the_mentor_prd/landing_page/code.html))
- `/login` — Login
- `/register` — Register
- `/onboarding/step/:step` — 5-step onboarding

All other routes will have stub components showing the page title.

